12.short_description: Social-emotional learning program for 2-to-6-year-old children. Play-based methodology. In-home delivery.

18.description:
Strong academic focus and standardization in school, limit children from developing the skills they need to be successful in the digital age.

Parents need after-school programs to complement their children’s development, but the existing offering is outdated and lacks personalization.

Our methodology, Future-Ready Learning Experiences, developed by experts, is designed to help children develop Core Life Skills in healthy, fun and personalized environments.

We are creating a tech-enabled community to connect teachers and parents at their own homes (e.g. Airbnb for after-school programs).

To achieve a balanced and enjoyable lifestyle, modern parents are increasingly looking for convenient and easy-to-access services, including their children’s education. To meet parents’ demands, we empower, professionalize and certify, a literal tribe of teachers (Trybü Guides) to provide Future-Ready Learning Experiences at children’s homes.

By 2029, we aim to empower and equip 100,000 young citizens for a fast-changing world.

Hexar provides a game-based learning platform on science, maths and skills to transform the way we teach and learn globally.

18.description:
We believe in creating a high-quality and motivating education, so that every child finds his or her passion and transforms the world through science and knowledge. That’s why we created Hexar: a social enterprise that provides a game-based learning platform on science, maths and skills for schools, teachers and students between 11 and 18 to transform the way we teach and learn globally through video games. 
Hexar seeks to educate the next generation of critical and proactive citizens. We substitute poor gamification that doesn't attract students with real video games. We combine game-based learning with: 
I) mobile accessibility
II) offline playability
III) metrics for teachers
IV) reports for parents
V) socio-emotional skills
VI) innovative learning frameworks. 
A solution in a meaningful format for both schools and teachers, and attractive to students.
